  {
    title: 'La Citadelle',
    slug: 'la-citadelle',
    featured: true,
    description: 'A premium Webflow website for La Citadelle de Québec, focused on elegant interactions, refined layouts, and a smooth editorial experience. The project combines minimalist visual direction with GSAP-powered scroll animations and Lottie animations, including line-based details that draw interface elements and illustrations as the user navigates through the site.',
    credit: 'Webflow development by Tito Solano as part of Uroboro.ca development team.',
    url: 'https://www.lacitadelle.qc.ca/',
    industry: 'Museum / Cultural Institution',
    year: 2024,
    role: 'Lead Webflow Developer & Integration Developer',
    challenge: 'The main challenge was bringing a clean and elegant design to life through subtle but meaningful interactions. The site needed to feel refined and premium, while keeping the navigation clear, responsive, and easy for the client to manage.',
    approach: 'I developed the Webflow build with a focus on layout precision, responsive behavior, and scroll-based animation. GSAP and Lottie were used to create controlled transitions, animated details, and drawing effects, while the CMS structure allows the client to easily update events, content, and key sections of the website.',
    keyFeatures: [
      'GSAP and Lottie animations for scroll-based motion and visual details',
      'CMS structure for simple content and event management',
      'Responsive implementation across key layouts',
