    approach: 'I developed the interface and interaction logic around how users would physically explore the application on a screen. The system connects Webflow with Xano as the backend database, allowing users to search and filter records by name, year, letter, category, and other criteria while keeping the experience fast, visual, and easy to use.',
    keyFeatures: [
      'Built an app-like archive experience inside Webflow.',
      'Designed interactions around touch-screen usability.',
      'Connected Webflow with Xano for searchable database logic.',
      'Supported bilingual content and interface switching.',
      'Added light and dark mode for different viewing contexts.',
    ],
    coverImage: '/images/morrin.avif',
    coverImageAlt: 'Person pointing at a tablet screen displaying a bright orange page titled Registre d\'Écrou.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Jeune Chambre De Commerce De Québec',
    slug: 'jccq',
    featured: true,
    description: 'A dynamic Webflow website developed from an existing visual direction, focused on expressive layouts, animations, and a strong member-centered experience. Beyond the visual build, the project included advanced web app functionality for community voting and promotion claims, supported by Xano, Wized, custom JavaScript, and Make automations.',
    credit: 'Webflow development by Tito Solano as part of Uroboro.ca development team.',
    url: 'https://www.jccq.qc.ca/',
    industry: 'Professional Network / Community',
    year: 2024,
    role: 'Lead Developer & Webflow',
    challenge: 'The main challenge was translating a bold, animated design into a responsive and scalable website while also supporting more advanced application-like functionality. The project required careful decisions around layout structure, animation behavior, CMS organization, data flows, and integrations.',
    approach: 'I led the development of the website structure, animations, CMS collections, and technical integrations. The voting and promotion claim systems were built as custom web app features, using Xano for backend and database logic, Wized to connect Webflow with dynamic functionality, and Make to automate workflows and data updates.',
    keyFeatures: [
      'Technical architecture for advanced web app functionality inside Webflow',
      'Dynamic systems for voting, promotion claims, submissions, validations, and data updates',
      'Backend logic powered by Xano, Wized, JavaScript, and Make',
