    coverImageAlt: 'Robotic arms holding a screen displaying JCCA logo in a dim industrial space with concrete walls.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Safari Condo',
    slug: 'safari-condo',
    featured: true,
    description: 'A Webflow website developed from an existing creative direction with a highly original layout, rich layering, and scroll-based storytelling. My role was to lead the development and solve the technical execution behind its most distinctive interactions, including a road-inspired route animation that follows the user through the experience.',
    credit: 'Webflow development by Tito Solano as part of Uroboro.ca development team.',
    url: 'https://www.safaricondo.com/',
    industry: 'Automotive / Travel',
    year: 2024,
    role: 'Lead Developer & Webflow',
    challenge: 'The main challenge was translating a very distinctive visual design into a responsive, animated, and maintainable website. The design included complex layering, organic and geometric shapes, SVG-based components, and scroll interactions that required an initial engineering phase before full development.',
    approach: 'I led the development and built most of the site, starting by solving the most complex layout and interaction patterns. The build used SVG, GSAP, Lottie, and Swiper.js to preserve the original design intent while keeping the experience smooth, flexible, and manageable inside Webflow.',
    keyFeatures: [
      'Scroll-based route animation inspired by a travel map',
      'Custom SVG shapes, cards, and layered visual elements',
      'GSAP, Lottie, and Swiper.js integrations',
      'Robust CMS for products, manuals, news, blog posts, and stores',
      'Geolocation logic for country-specific content',
