    title: 'Wendake',
    slug: 'wendake',
    featured: true,
    description: 'A large-scale community platform created for the Huron-Wendat Nation, designed to help visitors and residents discover cultural experiences, activities, events, accommodations, businesses, services, and community resources through a unified digital ecosystem.',
    credit: 'Webflow development by Tito Solano as part of Uroboro.ca development team.',
    url: 'https://www.wendake.ca/',
    industry: 'Culture & Community',
    year: 2025,
    role: 'Lead Developer & Webflow',
    challenge: 'The main challenge was organizing a large content ecosystem in a way that felt intuitive, accessible, and easy to navigate, while also supporting custom favorites, advanced commerce, and operational workflows beyond a traditional marketing website.',
    approach: 'The project was built on a structured CMS architecture designed to manage a broad content ecosystem with clarity and scalability. It included filtering, content relationships, a custom local favorites system, and an advanced Foxy e-commerce setup supported by Airtable and Make automation workflows.',
    keyFeatures: [
      'Large-scale CMS architecture',
      'Custom favorites system',
      'Advanced Foxy e-commerce implementation',
      'Airtable-powered data workflows',
      'Make automation integrations',
